p.-text Documentation and examples for Chi typography.

h3 Grid

p.-text All components in Chi, including Typography, adhere to a 4px baseline grid. The grid promotes consistency and familiarity through repetition. Chi achieves this repetition by ensuring line-height, padding, border, and margin values are divisible by 4. For user friendliness, Chi utilizes rem units instead of pixels. A rem is a unit of measurement that is equal to the root html font-size. Chi's root is 16px. So 1rem equals 16px.

h3 Typeface

p.-text The sans-serif font stack is used to display all typography within Chi except code. For code, Chi defers to a monospace font stack.

h6 Sans-serif font stack

.-mb--2
  :code(lang='html')
    font-family: "Open Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;

h6 Monospace font stack

.-mb--3
   :code(lang='html')
     font-family: Menlo, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Courier, monospace;

h3 Headings

p.-text Headings are used to illustrate the typographic hierarchy of a page. <code>h1</code> defines the most important heading and h6 the least. Headings in Chi can be defined as tags <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> - <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> or classes <code>.a-h1</code> - <code>.a-h6</code>.

section.a-table.-bordered.-mt--3.-mb--3
  div
    table(cellpadding='0', cellspacing='0')
      thead
        tr
          th
            div Heading
          th
            div Example
      tbody
        each type in ['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6']
          tr
            td(width='20%')
              code= '<' + type + '>'
            td
              #{type}= type + ' Chi heading'

