h3 Code
h4 Inline code
p.-text Code tags are used to wrap inline snippets of code.
.example.-mb--3
  p.-text.-m--3
    | This <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> will render as inline code.
  :code(lang="html")
    This <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> will render as inline code.
h4 Code blocks
p.-text Pre tags are used to wrap multiple lines of code.
.example.-mb--3
  .code-block.-m--3
    pre
      code &lt;p&gt;This code will render as a code block.&lt;/p&gt;
  :code(lang="html")
    <pre>
      <code>&lt;p&gt;This code will render as a code block.&lt;/p&gt;</code>
    </pre>

h3 Lists
h4 Base
p.-text Use <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> tags for unordered lists and <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> tags for ordered lists.
.a-grid
  .a-col.-w--6
    .example.-mb--3
      ul.-text
        li List item 1
        li List item 2
          ul
            li List item 2.1
            li List item 2.2
        li List item 3
        li List item 4
      :code(lang="html")
        <ul class="-text">
          <li></li>
        </ul>
  .a-col.-w--6
    .example.-mb--3
      ol.-text
        li List item 1
        li List item 2
          ul
            li List item 2.1
            li List item 2.2
        li List item 3
        li List item 4
      :code(lang="html")
        <ol class="-text">
          <li></li>
        </ol>
h4 No style
p.-text To remove default list styling, apply the class <code>.-nostyle</code>
.example.-mb--3
  ul.-text.-nostyle.-m--3
    li List item 1
    li List item 2
      ul.-nostyle
        li List item 2.1
        li List item 2.2
    li List item 3
    li List item 4
  :code(lang="html")
    <ul class="-text -nostyle">
      <li></li>
    </ul>
h4 Inline
p.-text To display list items inline, apply the class <code>.-inline</code>
.example.-mb--3
  ul.-text.-inline.-m--3
    li List item 1
    li List item 2
      ul.-inline
        li List item 2.1
        li List item 2.2
    li List item 3
    li List item 4
  :code(lang="html")
    <ul class="-text -inline">
      <li></li>
    </ul>
h3 Blockquotes
p.-text Blockquotes are used to quote content from another source.
.example.-mb--3
  blockquote.-m--3
    p.-text Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum lacus lacus, dictum quis mauris vel, commodo condimentum odio. Praesent lacus metus, vehicula at orci ac, fringilla mollis mauris.
  :code(lang="html")
    <blockquote>
      <p class="-text">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum lacus lacus, dictum quis mauris vel, commodo condimentum odio. Praesent lacus metus, vehicula at orci ac, fringilla mollis mauris.</p>
    </blockquote>
h3 Text alignment
p.-text Change text alignment to justified, left, center, or right.
.example.-mb--3
  .-m--3
    p.-text.-text--justify This text will render as justified
    p.-text.-text--left This text will render as left aligned
    p.-text.-text--center This text will render as center aligned
    p.-text.-text--right This text will render as right aligned
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-text--justify">This text will render as justified</p>
      <p class="-text--left">This text will render as left aligned</p>
      <p class="-text--center">This text will render as center aligned</p>
      <p class="-text--right">This text will render as right aligned</p>
h3 Text transform
p.-text Change text transform to lowercase, uppercase, or capitalized.
.example.-mb--3
  .-m--3
    p.-text.-text--lowercase This text will render as lowercase
    p.-text.-text--uppercase This text will render as uppercase
    p.-text.-text--capitalized This text will render as capitalized
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-text--lowercase">This text will render as lowercase</p>
      <p class="-text--uppercase">This text will render as uppercase</p>
      <p class="-text--capitalized">This text will render as capitalized</p>
h3 Text weight
p.-text Change text weight to thin, normal, bold, or bolder.
.example.-mb--3
  .-m--3
    p.-text.-text--thin This text will render as thin
    p.-text.-text--normal This text will render as normal
    p.-text.-text--bold This text will render as bold
    p.-text.-text--bolder This text will render as bolder
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-text--thin">This text will render as thin</p>
      <p class="-text--normal">This text will render as normal</p>
      <p class="-text--bold">This text will render as bold</p>
      <p class="-text--bolder">This text will render as bolder</p>
h3 Text wrapping
p.-text Prevent text wrapping with nowrap or control overflow with truncate.
.example.-mb--3
  .-m--3
    p.-text.-text--nowrap(style="width: 11rem;background:#eeeeee;") This text will render without wrapping
    p.-text.-text--truncate(style="width: 11rem;") This text will truncate with an ellipsis
  :code(lang="html")
      <p class="-text--nowrap">This text will render without wrapping</p>
      <p class="-text--truncate">This text will truncate with an ellipsis</p>
h3 Text colors
p.-text Change text colors with contextual classes.
.example.-mb--3
  .-m--3
    p.-text.-text--brand .-text--brand
    p.-text.-text--success .-text--success
    p.-text.-text--warning .-text--warning
    p.-text.-text--danger .-text--danger
    p.-text.-text--info .-text--info
    p.-text.-text--muted .-text--muted
    p.-text.-text--inverse(style="background:#000;") .-text--inverse
